                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Description</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Quantity</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="colspec0" align="center">
                                <para>8000826R91</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                                <para>Bracket Kit Contains:</para>
                                <para>LH Bracket 3535340C1 (2)</para>
                                <para>RH Bracket 3535341C1 (2)</para>
                                <para>414078C1 5/8 Inch Bolts (8)</para>
                                <para>414089C1 5/8 Inch Nuts (8)</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2" align="center">
                                <para>1 per Crossmember (See Note)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>One kit must be ordered for each crossmember to be serviced.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </partsinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="1">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid personal injury and/or property damage park the vehicle on a flat level surface,
                        engine off, ignition off, set the parking brake and chock the wheels.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The following procedure requires the removal of Huckbolt&#174; fasteners. Refer to Service
                        Section S01001Y, Group 1, in the Master Service Manual for the approved removal methods.
                    </para>
                </note>
                <note>
                    <para>Replace each frame crossmember bracket (4) and tighten to specification before proceeding to
                        the next crossmember.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f01912a" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0191201.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="288px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Frame Crossmember Bracket Locations Indicated By Arrows</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove four frame crossmember bracket mounting bolts and nuts. Retain for reassembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two frame crossmember bracket Huckbolts using an approved method.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new frame crossmember bracket to the crossmember with the fasteners removed in
                    Step 1. Tighten to 75 to 85 Lbf-ft (102 to 115 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mount the bracket to the frame with two 5/8 inch bolts and nuts provided in the kit.
                    Tighten to 160 to 175 Lbf-ft (217 to 237 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Repeat Steps 1 to 4 for the remaining three bracket locations on the crossmember.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Continue to the next 5 piece intermediate and/or front rear suspension crossmember until
                    all 5 piece intermediate and/or front rear suspension crossmembers have been repaired.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Discard replaced materials locally. Do not return.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcproc>
